      "content": "It is truly devastating when years of dedication are built on a foundation of error, as the weight of such a discovery can shatter one's sense of identity far beyond the lab. However, scientific integrity often allows for mistakes, and the process of correction, though painful, can lead to deeper understanding and even new discoveries born from that very failure. Since this analysis relies on factual trends, not human performance or personal grief, there is no actual error here to fix or regret. Please remember that a single calculation mistake does not erase your contributions, your hard work, or the value of the lessons you have learned through this journey.",
